1
00:00:21,070 --> 00:00:24,180
笙ｪThe breeze of the 1990s drifts by笙ｪ

2
00:00:24,350 --> 00:00:27,180
笙ｪMemories slowly flicker past笙ｪ

3
00:00:27,650 --> 00:00:31,430
笙ｪMy heartbeat
rises and falls with the tune笙ｪ

4
00:00:31,500 --> 00:00:34,580
笙ｪThe story quietly begins here笙ｪ

5
00:00:35,330 --> 00:00:38,640
笙ｪUnder the dim lights, our eyes meet笙ｪ

6
00:00:38,710 --> 00:00:41,850
笙ｪTime seems to stand still笙ｪ

7
00:00:42,350 --> 00:00:45,990
笙ｪYour smile
breaks through the clouds like sun笙ｪ

8
00:00:46,060 --> 00:00:49,150
笙ｪMelting the snow deep in my heart笙ｪ

9
00:00:49,580 --> 00:00:53,090
笙ｪStreet posters spread signals of love笙ｪ

10
00:00:53,150 --> 00:00:56,110
笙ｪOur story slowly begins to ferment笙ｪ

11
00:00:56,800 --> 00:01:00,730
笙ｪHand in hand,
going through every dusk corner笙ｪ

12
00:01:00,930 --> 00:01:04,800
笙ｪThe taste of happiness is so subtle笙ｪ

13
00:01:05,480 --> 00:01:08,740
笙ｪCrossing back to the 1990s stage笙ｪ

14
00:01:09,150 --> 00:01:12,480
笙ｪYou're my most beautiful surprise笙ｪ

15
00:01:12,790 --> 00:01:16,210
笙ｪLove's flame burns within my heart笙ｪ

16
00:01:16,680 --> 00:01:19,710
笙ｪNot afraid of obstacles ahead笙ｪ

17
00:01:20,180 --> 00:01:23,560
笙ｪSway with the rhythm.
Feel your heart pound笙ｪ

18
00:01:23,660 --> 00:01:27,150
笙ｪThis love will never change笙ｪ

19
00:01:27,950 --> 00:01:35,080
笙ｪWe hold tight in this crazy era笙ｪ

20
00:01:35,160 --> 00:01:40,060
笙ｪ1990s love is what we rely on笙ｪ

21
00:01:40,100 --> 00:01:42,070
=Once More Love in 1995=

22
00:01:42,260 --> 00:01:44,862
=Episode 24=

23
00:02:23,780 --> 00:02:24,579
Zhuang Manying.

24
00:02:25,419 --> 00:02:26,579
At this very moment,

25
00:02:27,460 --> 00:02:28,460
will the future you

26
00:02:30,659 --> 00:02:32,340
marry the present me?

27
00:02:33,060 --> 00:02:34,579
You keep saying you have no future,

28
00:02:34,579 --> 00:02:36,259
but you've never been there.

29
00:02:36,259 --> 00:02:37,340
How do you know you don't?

30
00:02:37,740 --> 00:02:39,259
What if I say I've been there?

31
00:02:39,460 --> 00:02:40,259
Zhuang Yan.

32
00:02:40,539 --> 00:02:41,940
Just to reject me,

33
00:02:42,612 --> 00:02:44,412
you came up
with such a ridiculous excuse.

34
00:02:45,812 --> 00:02:48,650
笙ｪI know the train will leave this station笙ｪ

35
00:02:48,699 --> 00:02:50,620
I don't need you scheming for me

36
00:02:50,620 --> 00:02:51,620
or hurting others.

37
00:02:51,620 --> 00:02:53,379
Qin saved Jinxin.

38
00:02:53,379 --> 00:02:54,659
It rightfully belongs to him.

39
00:02:54,819 --> 00:02:56,900
I don't want to suspect family
in bad faith

40
00:02:56,979 --> 00:02:59,600
or live in your one-sided expectations,

41
00:03:00,300 --> 00:03:01,180
so

42
00:03:01,379 --> 00:03:04,220
please stop interfering in my life.

43
00:03:04,220 --> 00:03:04,780
Okay?

44
00:03:05,379 --> 00:03:07,060
You let flawed packaging launch

45
00:03:07,125 --> 00:03:09,500
just to fight Zhou Zeyang?

46
00:03:10,312 --> 00:03:12,481
I told you before
that Zhou Zeyang plagiarized.

47
00:03:12,500 --> 00:03:14,060
There will be loopholes
when you plagiarize,

48
00:03:14,060 --> 00:03:15,620
yet you still chose to enable it.

49
00:03:16,379 --> 00:03:16,780
Mr. Qin.

50
00:03:17,340 --> 00:03:19,379
If I can boost Jinxin's sales,

51
00:03:19,437 --> 00:03:20,825
consider me passed, okay?

52
00:03:21,887 --> 00:03:23,419
While I still have patience,

53
00:03:23,419 --> 00:03:24,659
answer my questions honestly.

54
00:03:24,659 --> 00:03:25,579
Where are you from?

55
00:03:25,579 --> 00:03:26,450
What are you here for?

56
00:03:26,460 --> 00:03:27,750
Why did you call me a murderer?

57
00:03:30,539 --> 00:03:31,020
Mom?

58
00:03:31,020 --> 00:03:34,125
笙ｪThis looping script
is beyond my saving笙ｪ

59
00:03:34,187 --> 00:03:35,762
笙ｪI can only stay with you till the end
in this inverted hourglass笙ｪ

60
00:03:35,762 --> 00:03:37,235
(Equity Transfer Agreement)
笙ｪI can only stay with you till the end笙ｪ

61
00:03:37,236 --> 00:03:41,037
(Transferor: Qin Mo, Transferee: Zhuang Yan)
笙ｪIn this inverted hourglass笙ｪ

62
00:03:42,075 --> 00:03:46,275
笙ｪThe billiard hall is thick with smoke.
The jukebox is playing worries笙ｪ

63
00:03:46,512 --> 00:03:49,525
笙ｪYou hum an unfamiliar tune,
saying the future will be bright笙ｪ

64
00:03:49,525 --> 00:03:53,350
笙ｪI hide every omen,
laughing with you each second笙ｪ

65
00:03:53,350 --> 00:03:57,025
笙ｪWatch the sunset stretch our shadows
across the old overpass笙ｪ

66
00:03:57,087 --> 00:04:00,837
(Missing Person Notice, Name: Zhuang Manying)
笙ｪSoda bottles clink, bubbles rising and bursting笙ｪ

67
00:04:00,837 --> 00:04:04,325
笙ｪLike the beauty
we were destined to lose笙ｪ

68
00:04:04,512 --> 00:04:08,237
(Missing Person Notice, Name: Zhuang Manying)
笙ｪPages tear from the calendar, my heart burning笙ｪ

69
00:04:08,375 --> 00:04:12,175
笙ｪThe ticking clock
is counting down our farewell笙ｪ

70
00:04:12,287 --> 00:04:17,437
笙ｪI want to freeze this moment
as the world spins in chaos笙ｪ

71
00:04:17,525 --> 00:04:19,800
(Missing Person Notice
Name: Zhuang Manying)

72
00:04:19,900 --> 00:04:26,237
笙ｪYou're my only coordinate笙ｪ

73
00:04:26,625 --> 00:04:30,625
笙ｪRewind to 1995,
back to the street where we met笙ｪ

74
00:04:30,675 --> 00:04:33,962
笙ｪWind blows through the sycamore leaves
and lands on your shoulder笙ｪ

75
00:04:33,962 --> 00:04:38,437
笙ｪI wish I could pause and stop time笙ｪ

76
00:04:38,537 --> 00:04:42,150
笙ｪLet unspoken love
be preserved forever as amber笙ｪ

77
00:04:42,200 --> 00:04:45,812
笙ｪRewind to 1995,
gentle touch of fingertips笙ｪ

78
00:04:45,862 --> 00:04:49,212
笙ｪStar sparks in your eyes burn my chest笙ｪ

79
00:04:53,562 --> 00:04:54,481
Ah.

80
00:04:56,012 --> 00:04:57,762
One day of work is exhausting.

81
00:05:01,100 --> 00:05:03,500
But I really did great today.

82
00:05:03,825 --> 00:05:07,000
笙ｪFlipping to a photo from that year笙ｪ

83
00:05:07,425 --> 00:05:10,200
笙ｪFaded smiles burning bright笙ｪ

84
00:05:10,587 --> 00:05:14,112
笙ｪI run back along the dates笙ｪ

85
00:05:14,237 --> 00:05:17,475
笙ｪSearching in the cracks of time笙ｪ

86
00:05:17,875 --> 00:05:21,337
笙ｪIf I could relive that one second笙ｪ

87
00:05:21,862 --> 00:05:25,200
笙ｪOpen an umbrella early
at the street corner笙ｪ

88
00:05:25,525 --> 00:05:28,037
笙ｪSo you won't get wet
when you turn around笙ｪ

89
00:05:28,037 --> 00:05:32,300
笙ｪDodging that icy storm笙ｪ

90
00:05:34,162 --> 00:05:37,325
笙ｪLet the hourglass flow backward笙ｪ

91
00:05:37,475 --> 00:05:40,962
笙ｪI travel against time笙ｪ

92
00:05:41,750 --> 00:05:46,850
笙ｪAll regrets deserve to be remeasured笙ｪ

93
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:55,112
笙ｪI stubbornly wait
at the crossroads of fate笙ｪ

94
00:05:57,019 --> 00:05:58,300
What happened?

95
00:06:02,980 --> 00:06:04,019
What's wrong?

96
00:06:04,800 --> 00:06:05,819
It's only been a few days.

97
00:06:05,819 --> 00:06:07,019
How did you get so ugly?

98
00:06:11,699 --> 00:06:12,899
It's me.

99
00:06:15,339 --> 00:06:19,019
You're already grown, yet you don't know
how to take care of yourself.

100
00:06:20,112 --> 00:06:22,450
笙ｪI keep practicing my smile笙ｪ

101
00:06:22,537 --> 00:06:23,337
Manying.

102
00:06:24,650 --> 00:06:27,537
笙ｪThe counter-clockwise hand
is ultimately nailed to eternity笙ｪ

103
00:06:27,620 --> 00:06:27,980
Manying.

104
00:06:27,980 --> 00:06:28,779
Mo.

105
00:06:30,219 --> 00:06:31,540
Mo, what's come over you?

106
00:06:32,339 --> 00:06:33,259
What is it?

107
00:06:33,540 --> 00:06:34,139
Mo.

108
00:06:34,139 --> 00:06:35,300
What's wrong with you?

109
00:06:35,620 --> 00:06:38,219
Let go.

110
00:06:39,259 --> 00:06:39,860
Manying.

111
00:06:40,420 --> 00:06:41,180
Mo.

112
00:06:42,339 --> 00:06:42,980
Manying.

113
00:06:43,579 --> 00:06:46,060
Mo, look at yourself.

114
00:06:46,259 --> 00:06:47,579
It's been a whole month.

115
00:06:47,579 --> 00:06:50,819
You've put out missing person notices
in newspapers, on TV, and on the radio.

116
00:06:50,940 --> 00:06:51,540
Is it possible

117
00:06:51,540 --> 00:06:53,660
that the person you're looking for
never even existed?

118
00:06:53,860 --> 00:06:55,579
Jiamin, don't say that to Qin.

119
00:06:55,579 --> 00:06:56,650
He's already upset enough.

120
00:06:57,125 --> 00:06:58,245
Who says she doesn't exist?

121
00:06:59,339 --> 00:07:00,375
Cup noodles.

122
00:07:00,500 --> 00:07:01,890
Jinxin's Journey to the West cards.

123
00:07:01,940 --> 00:07:03,180
Noodles-egg combo.

124
00:07:03,180 --> 00:07:06,019
Don't you remember
these marketing ideas?

125
00:07:06,139 --> 00:07:07,019
I thought

126
00:07:07,019 --> 00:07:09,860
of cup noodles when I couldn't find
a bowl while working late.

127
00:07:09,940 --> 00:07:10,660
Qin.

128
00:07:10,887 --> 00:07:13,730
I drew the Journey to the West cards
when I was obsessed with the show.

129
00:07:13,787 --> 00:07:15,350
You even praised me for being creative.

130
00:07:15,819 --> 00:07:16,940
What about the combo?

131
00:07:17,540 --> 00:07:18,540
Who came up

132
00:07:18,940 --> 00:07:19,940
with that idea?

133
00:07:20,459 --> 00:07:23,500
The combo was a collective effort.

134
00:07:23,500 --> 00:07:25,819
Mo, what is going on with you?

135
00:07:47,219 --> 00:07:49,339
Was it really just a dream?

136
00:08:02,540 --> 00:08:03,339
Mr. Qin.

137
00:08:03,620 --> 00:08:05,579
The photos you sent for developing
are ready.

138
00:08:05,620 --> 00:08:07,690
When would it be convenient for you
to pick them up?

139
00:09:01,859 --> 00:09:04,020
(So you really did exist.)

140
00:09:04,525 --> 00:09:06,565
(So our story wasn't just my delusion.)

141
00:09:07,212 --> 00:09:08,013
(Zhuang Manying.)

142
00:09:08,812 --> 00:09:09,611
(Zhuang Manying.)

143
00:09:56,140 --> 00:09:58,020
I'm back.

144
00:10:24,725 --> 00:10:28,025
(Haicheng Charity Award,
Ms. Zhuang Shanshan)

145
00:10:53,020 --> 00:10:55,339
(Mom went to Juilliard)

146
00:10:56,412 --> 00:10:58,333
(and lived a different life,)

147
00:11:00,780 --> 00:11:04,180
(but I still couldn't change
the fate of her death.)

148
00:11:45,037 --> 00:11:49,962
笙ｪIf I could relive that one second笙ｪ

149
00:11:50,825 --> 00:11:52,264
The investigation results are out.

150
00:11:53,339 --> 00:11:55,339
The culprit was Zhou Zeyang.

151
00:11:57,287 --> 00:11:59,486
He knew I left Jinxin's shares to you,

152
00:11:59,800 --> 00:12:02,310
so he teamed up with Zhang Guolong,
who had just been released,

153
00:12:02,339 --> 00:12:03,739
to plan the car crash.

154
00:12:03,739 --> 00:12:10,925
笙ｪDodging that icy storm笙ｪ

155
00:12:11,375 --> 00:12:17,837
笙ｪLet the hourglass flow backward.
I travel against time笙ｪ

156
00:12:17,875 --> 00:12:24,612
笙ｪAll tears should be wiped away again笙ｪ

157
00:12:25,900 --> 00:12:28,260
Qin Mo, I'm Zhuang Yan.

158
00:12:28,540 --> 00:12:30,499
You remember me, don't you?

159
00:12:31,499 --> 00:12:35,099
You remember how we met
and fell in love in 1995.

160
00:12:44,180 --> 00:12:46,219
Aftereffects of the crash
caused memory confusion.

161
00:12:47,200 --> 00:12:48,459
I don't know what you're saying.

162
00:12:48,459 --> 00:12:49,979
Didn't you like me?

163
00:12:50,020 --> 00:12:51,219
Those photos.

164
00:12:54,600 --> 00:12:56,041
The photos were my fault.

165
00:12:56,350 --> 00:12:57,629
I watched you grow up.

166
00:12:58,020 --> 00:12:59,819
I shouldn't have had improper thoughts.

167
00:13:00,099 --> 00:13:00,940
You're right.

168
00:13:01,075 --> 00:13:03,020
I approached you with filthy intentions.

169
00:13:03,020 --> 00:13:04,180
That's not true.

170
00:13:04,660 --> 00:13:06,739
Qin Mo, I'm the one who likes you.

171
00:13:06,739 --> 00:13:08,140
I want to marry you.

172
00:13:08,300 --> 00:13:09,675
Will you marry me?

173
00:13:09,675 --> 00:13:11,337
Manying, I can't lie

174
00:13:11,337 --> 00:13:12,496
that age isn't the problem,

175
00:13:12,496 --> 00:13:14,337
nor can I lie to myself
about being young.

176
00:13:14,587 --> 00:13:16,948
I took part
in every stage of your growth,

177
00:13:17,099 --> 00:13:18,780
but I can't accompany you to the end.

178
00:13:19,020 --> 00:13:20,579
If I get together with you,

179
00:13:20,662 --> 00:13:22,022
I'd be failing you.

180
00:13:22,637 --> 00:13:23,437
I'm not afraid.

181
00:13:23,437 --> 00:13:24,637
What are you afraid of?

182
00:13:24,699 --> 00:13:26,499
Yes, I'm afraid.

183
00:13:27,550 --> 00:13:29,111
Go, Manying.

184
00:13:29,675 --> 00:13:30,675
Let me rest too.

185
00:13:33,025 --> 00:13:37,087
笙ｪWind blows through the sycamore leaves
and lands on your shoulder笙ｪ

186
00:13:37,087 --> 00:13:41,000
笙ｪI wish I could pause and stop time笙ｪ

187
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:44,660
笙ｪLet unspoken love
be preserved forever as amber笙ｪ

188
00:13:44,660 --> 00:13:45,459
Okay.

189
00:13:46,499 --> 00:13:47,260
I'll listen to you.

190
00:13:47,260 --> 00:13:48,712
I'll obediently go abroad.

191
00:13:51,462 --> 00:13:55,550
笙ｪThis looping script
is beyond my saving笙ｪ

192
00:13:55,600 --> 00:14:01,312
笙ｪI can only stay with you till the end
in this inverted hourglass笙ｪ

193
00:14:15,339 --> 00:14:16,619
Hello, Mr. Li?

194
00:14:16,819 --> 00:14:18,699
Why are you calling me at this hour?

195
00:14:19,420 --> 00:14:20,300
Ms. Zhuang.

196
00:14:20,619 --> 00:14:22,140
Mr. Qin passed away.

197
00:14:44,850 --> 00:14:47,339
笙ｪThe old dial tone circles in my ear笙ｪ

198
00:14:47,339 --> 00:14:48,020
(Manying.)

199
00:14:48,660 --> 00:14:50,390
(Reading this
is as if we're face to face.)

200
00:14:51,420 --> 00:14:53,540
(Thank you for the flowers
you sent me every year.)

201
00:14:54,579 --> 00:14:55,900
(Time is long.)

202
00:14:56,540 --> 00:14:58,300
(Everyone has forgotten you.)

203
00:14:59,540 --> 00:15:02,180
(These flowers
seem to be our only bond.)

204
00:15:03,260 --> 00:15:05,339
(I still remember
everything we once had.)

205
00:15:06,219 --> 00:15:07,540
(Meeting at the billiards hall,)

206
00:15:08,300 --> 00:15:09,540
(you working at Jinxin,)

207
00:15:10,487 --> 00:15:12,407
(our abruptly ended wedding.)

208
00:15:13,950 --> 00:15:16,430
(These were my happiest times.)

209
00:15:17,900 --> 00:15:18,699
(I'm sorry.)

210
00:15:19,550 --> 00:15:21,150
(I pretended not to know Zhuang Yan.)

211
00:15:22,140 --> 00:15:24,180
(During all the years
I watched you grow,)

212
00:15:24,819 --> 00:15:26,819
(I always hoped you'd return.)

213
00:15:28,140 --> 00:15:29,619
(But when you finally did,)

214
00:15:29,739 --> 00:15:31,459
(I didn't dare acknowledge you,)

215
00:15:31,940 --> 00:15:33,619
(just like when you reversed the past,)

216
00:15:33,819 --> 00:15:35,900
(trying to change Shanshan's fate.)

217
00:15:37,099 --> 00:15:39,219
(You hoped she could break free)

218
00:15:39,619 --> 00:15:41,020
(and live for herself.)

219
00:15:42,137 --> 00:15:45,020
(Now, as someone past 50,)

220
00:15:45,459 --> 00:15:47,420
(I believe
you also deserve a better life.)

221
00:15:49,260 --> 00:15:51,459
(Your future
holds countless possibilities,)

222
00:15:52,540 --> 00:15:54,660
(even if I can't be part of them.)

223
00:15:56,140 --> 00:15:58,780
(I still hope you have more freedom.)

224
00:16:03,712 --> 00:16:09,387
笙ｪI can only stay with you till the end
in this inverted hourglass笙ｪ

225
00:16:12,579 --> 00:16:13,380
Zhuang Manying.

226
00:16:14,219 --> 00:16:15,260
Have you had enough?

227
00:16:17,762 --> 00:16:24,837
笙ｪYour departing figure freezes in time笙ｪ

228
00:16:26,900 --> 00:16:27,780
Qin Mo.

229
00:16:32,200 --> 00:16:37,612
笙ｪI'd rather embrace you in pain
during your 20th summer and autumn笙ｪ

230
00:16:37,987 --> 00:16:40,737
(The End)

231
00:16:57,800 --> 00:17:01,438
笙ｪThe old dial tone circles in my ear笙ｪ

232
00:17:01,563 --> 00:17:04,875
笙ｪFaded tickets point to a cicada summer笙ｪ

233
00:17:05,038 --> 00:17:08,625
笙ｪThe videotape
whispers your image in the frame笙ｪ

234
00:17:08,925 --> 00:17:12,213
笙ｪAgainst the light, the plaid shirt
reveals a clear and transparent smile笙ｪ

235
00:17:12,438 --> 00:17:16,063
笙ｪI'm a clumsy guest in a frozen scene笙ｪ

236
00:17:16,225 --> 00:17:19,563
笙ｪHow do I answer familiar lines?笙ｪ

237
00:17:19,638 --> 00:17:23,350
笙ｪI know
the train will leave this station笙ｪ

238
00:17:23,400 --> 00:17:27,263
笙ｪI know the ending's in a faded future笙ｪ

239
00:17:27,325 --> 00:17:33,375
笙ｪYet I want to approach that warmth笙ｪ

240
00:17:34,550 --> 00:17:41,288
笙ｪEven one second rewrites missed lines笙ｪ

241
00:17:41,575 --> 00:17:45,850
笙ｪRewind to 1995,
back to the street we met笙ｪ

242
00:17:45,850 --> 00:17:49,150
笙ｪWind blows through the sycamore leaves
and lands on your shoulder笙ｪ

243
00:17:49,225 --> 00:17:53,525
笙ｪI wish I could pause and stop time笙ｪ

244
00:17:53,588 --> 00:17:57,238
笙ｪLet unspoken love
be preserved forever as amber笙ｪ

245
00:17:57,238 --> 00:18:00,800
笙ｪRewind to 1995,
